3 L is to the right and above R at an angle of about 45 degrees.
4 What is the relation of the agent L to the agent R?	upper-left	1
1 The object G is upper and slightly to the right of the object L.
2 E is at a 45 degree angle to G, in the upper righthand corner.
3 E is placed at the bottom of Z.
4 What is the relation of the agent E to the agent Z?	above	1
1 U is to the left of C and below C at approximately a 45 degree angle.
2 X is to the left of C.
3 X is positioned left to I.
4 What is the relation of the agent I to the agent C?	overlap	1
1 B is at the 3 o'clock position relative to Z.
2 Y is directly south east of Z.
3 T is sitting at the upper right position to Y.
4 What is the relation of the agent Y to the agent Z?	lower-right	1
1 H presents lower left to I.
2 H is south east of V.
3 The object P and I are there. The object P is below and slightly to the right of the object I.
4 What is the relation of the agent P to the agent I?	lower-right	1
1 Y is diagonally left and above Y.
2 A is there and Y is at the 5 position of a clock face.
3 A is on the same horizontal plane directly left to D.
4 What is the relation of the agent W to the agent A?	lower-right	1
1 T is below K at 7 o'clock.
2 S and P are in a horizontal line with P on the right.
3 S is to the right and above T at an angle of about 45 degrees.
4 What is the relation of the agent S to the agent K?	left	1
1 O is over there and Q is directly below it.
2 N is directly above E.
3 E is positioned above O.
4 What is the relation of the agent N to the agent O?	above	1
1 M is over there with T above.
2 T is above and to the left of C.
3 F is on the same horizontal plane directly right to C.
4 What is the relation of the agent M to the agent C?	left	1
1 M is below V.
2 T is directly south east of H.
3 H and V are both there with the object H is to the left of object V.
4 What is the relation of the agent T to the agent M?	overlap	1
1 L is positioned in the top left corner of H.
2 H and Z are parallel, and H is to the right of Z.
3 L is diagonally left and above L.
4 What is the relation of the agent W to the agent L?	lower-right	1
1 The object D is positioned directly above the object A.
